{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"humourless-unartful-foal","description":"## Why\nThe ensure-registry (epic odd-vortex-elbow, landed) has per-surface tests, but no single\nsuite exercises the *differential* contract against a synthetic store that an OLDER rebar\ninitialized — one that is behind on arbitrary COMBINATIONS of the five ensure units and needs\ndifferent idempotent migration operations. Preserve a hermetic drift-matrix integration test so\nthe mechanism can be re-validated in the future as units are added or changed.\n\n## What\nAdd `tests/interfaces/store/test_ensure_drift_matrix.py`: fabricate legacy drift on a chosen\nsubset of {env-id, gc-config, merge-ours, gitattributes, gitignore} on a fresh isolated tracker\n(gc.auto=0 + autoDetach unset; merge.ours.driver unset; committed .gitattributes carrying the\nretired `.reconciler-* merge=ours` line; a stale committed .gitignore; deleted .env-id), then\nassert `run_ensures` corrects EXACTLY the drifted units. Hermetic: `tmp_path` tracker, sync off,\nno network.\n\nScenarios (parametrized): S0 converged, S1 legacy-gc, S2 no-merge-driver, S3 retired-\ngitattributes, S4 stale-gitignore, S5 no-env-id, S6 partial (gc+gitignore), S7 three-behind,\nS8 fully-legacy; plus the operator `fsck --repair` path on a fully-legacy store; plus a\npre-feature store (no marker) reported pending then repaired.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/store/test_ensure_drift_matrix.py` is hermetic (isolated `tmp_path` tracker, `REBAR_SYNC_*` off, no network) and runs in the default (non-integration/non-external) tier\n- [ ] Parametrized matrix asserts, per behind-subset: every drifted unit reports `changed`, every converged unit reports `ok`, none `failed`; the store reconverges (per-unit invariants: gc.auto unset + autoDetach=true, merge.ours.driver=true, no retired .gitattributes line, .gitignore ⊇ the expected set, .env-id present); only the two commit-units commit, and only when behind\n- [ ] Idempotency: a second `run_ensures` on each reconverged store is all `ok` and makes zero new commits (git-log assertion); `.ensure-applied` records all five ids\n- [ ] Operator path: `rebar fsck --repair` converges a fully-legacy store (reports 5 changed) and a second `--repair` reports `0 changed` / no new commits\n- [ ] Pre-feature store (no `.ensure-applied`) is reported `ensures: 0/5 applied` by read-only `fsck` and reaches `5/5` after `--repair`\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make typecheck` clean; the new file adds no over-cap module and no drift-gate regressions","id":"92ee-f773-8c06-4aa9","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Hermetic drift-matrix integration tests for the ensure-registry"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783652851497410001,"uuid":"ab76f09a-4b00-4889-b6cb-bbf13d00bb9e"}